# akpsi-app

A web app for the Alpha Kappa Psi (AKPsi) chapter at UW. Built for members, officers, and pledges to stay connected and organized.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 16 (App Router) with React 19 and TypeScript
- **UI:** shadcn/ui for components, Tailwind CSS 4 for all styling
- **Icons:** lucide-react
- **Backend:** Firebase (Auth, Firestore, Storage, Hosting)
- **Styling approach:** Use shadcn/ui components (`components/ui/`) for all interactive UI. Style with Tailwind utility classes. Use `cn()` from `lib/utils.ts` for conditional class merging. No MUI — it has been removed.

## Pages & Features

### 1. Announcements (`/announcements`)
- Feed of chapter announcements with title, body, author avatar, timestamp, and optional images
- Members can create announcements via a modal
- Stored in Firestore `announcements` collection
- Future: Slack channel integration to auto-pull announcements

### 2. Member Directory (`/members`)
- Searchable/sortable table of all members
- Self-supplied profiles: name, major, graduation year, pledge class, big, phone, email, bio, social links, industries
- Members control contact info visibility
- Stored in Firestore `members` collection (path: `users/{uid}`)

### 3. Gallery (`/gallery`)
- Pinterest-style masonry grid of chapter photos
- Members can upload photos with captions
- Lightbox for full-size viewing
- Stored in Firestore `gallery` collection; images in Firebase Storage

### 4. Family Tree (`/family-tree`)
- Interactive graph visualization of big/little relationships across pledge classes
- Built with `@xyflow/react`
- Currently uses mock data — Firebase integration pending

