## Firebase Setup

- Config loaded from env vars in `.env.local` (see `.env.local.example`)
- Firestore collections: `announcements`, `users` (members), `gallery`
- Storage paths: `announcements/{id}/{file}`, `gallery/{uid}/{file}`, `avatars/{uid}/{file}`
- Security rules: authenticated reads across all collections; writes scoped to document owner

## Conventions

### General
- `"use client"` only when the component uses hooks, events, or browser APIs — prefer Server Components
- All Firebase calls go through helpers in `lib/` — never call Firestore/Storage directly in components
- One component per file, named exports, PascalCase filenames for components
- Keep pages thin — delegate logic to components and hooks

### Styling
- Use shadcn/ui components from `components/ui/` for all interactive UI elements
- Style exclusively with Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use `cn()` from `lib/utils.ts` for conditional/merged class names
- Color tokens use CSS variables via Tailwind (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, etc.)
- No inline styles, no MUI, no `sx` prop

### File Header Comments
When creating a **new** functional code file, add a brief comment at the top (before imports):
1. What the file does — one sentence, plain language
2. Where it fits — what page, feature, or part of the app uses it

Keep it short (2–4 lines). No verbose JSDoc.

```tsx
// MemberRow — Renders a single row in the member directory table.
// Used by MemberTable on /members.
```

Applies to: components, pages, hooks, helpers, utilities, type definitions.
Does NOT apply to: config files, auto-generated files, env files, markdown, rule files.

### TypeScript
- Explicit return types on exported functions
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- Avoid `any` — use `unknown` and narrow, or define proper types
- Prefer `const` assertions and `readonly` where applicable

### React Components
- Functional components only, no classes
- Props interface named `[Component]Props`
- Destructure props in function signature
- Group hooks at top, then handlers, then render logic

### Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`MemberCard.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useAuth.ts`)
- Utils: camelCase (`formatDate.ts`)
- Types: PascalCase (`Member`, `Announcement`)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE

### Imports Order
1. React / Next.js
2. Third-party (Firebase, lucide-react, @xyflow/react, etc.)
3. Local components
4. Local utils / hooks
5. Types

